            "id": "4564070",
            "title": "Retail jolt: Amazon plans to move Prime Day into June for the first time",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Amazon (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMZN\" title=\"Amazon.com, Inc.\">AMZN</a></span></span>) plans to shift its annual Prime Day sale to late June from July, sources told Bloomberg. </p>\n<p>A timing change would have broad implications across the retailer sector as thousands of third-party vendors and competitors such as Walmart (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WMT\" title=\"Walmart Inc.\">WMT</a>), Target (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TGT\" title=\"Target Corporation\">TGT</a>), Costco (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COST\" title=\"Costco Wholesale Corporation\">COST</a>), Best Buy (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BBY\" title=\"Best Buy Co., Inc.\">BBY</a>), Dick's Sporting Goods (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DKS\" title=\"DICK'S Sporting Goods, Inc.\">DKS</a>), Etsy (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ETSY\" title=\"Etsy, Inc.\">ETSY</a>), Wayfair (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/W\" title=\"Wayfair Inc.\">W</a>) and Macy's (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/M\" title=\"Macy's, Inc.\">M</a>) consider if they need to change their summer schedules.</p>\n<p>Amazon Prime Day began on July 15, 2015, as a one-day global sales event created to celebrate the 20th anniversary of the company. Originally conceived as a members-only promotion for Prime subscribers, it promised \"more deals than Black Friday\" and initially ran for 24 hours across nine countries, including the United States, United Kingdom, Germany, and Japan.</p>\n<p>In the following years, Prime Day evolved from a single-day experiment into a multi-day, mid-summer retail fixture that Amazon (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMZN\" title=\"Amazon.com, Inc.\">AMZN</a>) used to drive both sales and Prime subscriptions. By the early 2020s, Prime Day had become one of the largest annual events in e-commerce, often surpassing Amazon's (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMZN\" title=\"Amazon.com, Inc.\">AMZN</a>) own Black Friday and Cyber Monday performance and reshaping the July promotions and sales events of competitors.</p>\n<p>Shares of Amazon (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMZN\" title=\"Amazon.com, Inc.\">AMZN</a>) edged 0.3% higher in postmarket trading after shedding 1.1% during the regular session.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
